author: cbc
title: Highway 39 blocked after collision near Moose Jaw
text:
Moose Jaw RCMP say Highway 39 has been blocked after a two-vehicle collision Sunday afternoon.
The collision occurred approximately five and a half kilometres south of Highway 1.
The highway will remain blocked while police conduct an investigation. It could potentially be reopened during the evening.
Motorists are being asked to use alternate routes such as Highways 1, 624 or 339 until further notice.
The police ask that anyone on the road exercise caution due to the winter conditions.
Reduced visibility, icy sections and lots of snow on Sask. highways Sunday
